<h2>right to property</h2>
<ul>
<li>history
<ul>
<li>initially , in original CoI, under articles 19(1)(f) 31(1) 31(2)</li>
<li>31A - as per 1st CAA, 1951
<ul>
<li>can acquire property of large estates And it will not violate 14 or 19(1) (f)</li></ul></li>
<li>31B - 9th schedule - property in it
<ul>
<li>no Judicial review</li></ul></li></ul></li>
<li>4th amendment
<ul>
<li>amended 31(2) = compensation amount cannot be questioned in court of law</li></ul></li>
<li>removed as FR in 44th amendment + 300A introduced
<ul>
<li>3001A = No person shall be deprived of his property save by authority of law.</li></ul></li>
<li>25th CAA, 1971 - permitted the acquisition of private property by the government for public use,
<ul>
<li>4th amendment is valid but REASONABLE compensation</li>
<li><a href="#ID_565218883" target="_blank">31C : 39(b) , 39(c) &gt; 14,19,31</a></li></ul></li>
<li>adverse possession', SC (2020)
<ul>
<li>welfare state cannot use it to grab private property :p</li></ul></li></ul>